I like this concept a lot. The part that made it work for me was when I reached the arguments against Asimov's laws, started thinking about exactly why they were dumb, and then realized what you were doing there. I think it still needs more work to reach the particular clinical tone of an SCP article, as there were a number of places where your choice of phrasing distracted me from your message. In particular, I think the Asimov argument should go in the addendum, rather than paraphrased in the description. I also feel like the robot triggering it because of DATA EXPUNGED is a bit of a cop out, since the missing data doesn't imply anything particularly interesting or frightening. Maybe it switched to Asimov because the engineer who built the robot was a fan.







